Direct plating of simulated stool specimens on MacConkey agar (MCA) with 10-mug ertapenem, meropenem, and imipenem disks allowed the establishment of optimal zone diameters for the screening of carbapenem-resistant Gram-negative rods (CRGNR) of </= 24 mm (ertapenem), </= 34 mm (meropenem), and </= 32 mm (imipenem).